\begin{center}
Laplace Transform $\mathcal L$\\
\vspace{.2cm}
For constants $a,b,c \in \mathbb R$, arbitrary real functions $f$ and $g$, integer $n$, real number $p>-1$.\\
\begin{tabular}{ | c | c | c | c |}
\hline
Time & Frequency & Time & Frequency \\
\hline
$f(t)$ & $\mathcal L[f](s)$ & $\mathcal L^{-1}[F](t)$ & $F(s)$ \\
\hline
$f+g$ & $\mathcal L[f]+\mathcal L[g]$ & $cf$ & $c\mathcal L[f]$\\
\hline
$f'$ & $s\mathcal L[f]-f(0)$ & $f^{(n)}$ & $s^nF(s) -\sum_{k=0}^{n-1} s^{n-k} f^{(k)}(0)$ \\
\hline
 $t^nf(t)$ & $(-1)^nF^{(n)}(s)$ & $f \ast g $ & $\mathcal L [f] \mathcal L [g]$ \\
 \hline
 $1$ & $\frac 1 s$ & $\delta(t-c)$ & $e^{-cs}$\\
\hline
 $e^{at}$ & $\frac 1 {s-a}$ & $e^{ct}f(t)$ & $F(s-c)$ \\
\hline
$t^n$ & $\frac{n!}{s^{n+1}}$ & $t^p$ & $\frac{\Gamma(p+1)}{s^{p+1}}$ \\
\hline
$\sin at$ & $\frac{1}{s^2+a^2}$ & $\cos at$ & $\frac{s}{s^2+a^2}$ \\
\hline
$\sinh at$ & $\frac{1}{s^2-a^2}$ & $\cosh at$ & $\frac{s}{s^2-a^2}$ \\
\hline
$u(t-c)$ & $\frac{e^{-cs}}{s}$ & $u(t-c)f(t-c)$ & $e^{-cs}F(s)$ \\
\hline
\end{tabular}
\end{center}
